@sara.choi grew up in a Korean-American family in Hawaii. At 15, she found refuge with a group of “car kids,” spending nights at Oahu cruise meets and working at a local tuning shop.

In her early 20s, she moved to Osaka, was mentored by a professional driver and later transitioned from street racing to competitive drifting. Today she competes across Asia and still builds her own cars.

She uses ChatGPT like both a mechanic and a strategist, helping her fine-tune drift-car alignment and wheel-spec setups while also managing her competition calendar and reviewing sponsor offers. See 4 of her favorite chats.

